column2: On Screen and Off Screen, Johnny Depp just does not portray the type of character that Amber is insinuating. Through the libel case, she has only more to gain than to lose, which is likely why she did what she did. Which turned out to be true from the increase in financing, commercial support, social backing and even career advancements. Depp was persecuted with much male-stereotypical prejudice. The proof that Amber also had displayed much abuse was mooted. There is no justice presently. We have to stand for what is unbiased and true, and not what our humanly stereotypical ideals are. Men can be hurt too. Women can also be perpetrators. Men can also be telling the truth. Women can also tell lies.

column2:
She is a husband beater and blatant liar and the evidence shows this.

She is not that good an actress and only got where she is because she married Johnny Depp.

Yes she is stunning to look at but she is and has an evil inside.

This woman does not deserve to have this roll after using someone else's experience of spousal abuse to use against her ex husband.
It is despicable and as I am English the law in this country is an ass as they are too scared to stand up against a woman alleging falsehoods against a man. 

Men too can be abused by their wives.

The judge in the appeal is an old fool and should be ashamed of himself.

column2:
This is an important issue that needs to be resolved. 

When there is clear evidence of someone lying about abuse and deliberately ruining someone's reputation and career, and the evidence clearly points opposite...

I can see no other reason for the treatment that Johnny Depp has received other than sexism.

True feminism is about equality and realization that both men and women can be victims of abuse from a woman or a man.

Amber heard is causing horrible damage to women who have actually been abused.

The obviously unjust desicion where the judge wasn't objective, and gave no reason for dismissing evidence, causes horrible damage for men seeking justice from abuse.

The double standards of the movie industry is encouraging False Claims and character assassination, and making it harder for real cases to be heard.
